020import java.lang.constant.MethodTypeDesc;
021
022import java.util.Arrays;
023import java.util.Collection;
024import java.util.Iterator;
025import java.util.List;
026import java.util.Objects;
027import java.util.TreeSet;
028
029import java.util.function.Function;
030
031import static java.lang.constant.ConstantDescs.CD_Collection;
032
033import static java.lang.constant.DirectMethodHandleDesc.Kind.STATIC;
034
035import static org.microbean.qualifier.ConstantDescs.CD_Iterable;
036import static org.microbean.qualifier.ConstantDescs.CD_Qualifiers;

038/**
039 * An immutable {@link Bindings} containing {@link Qualifier}
040 * instances.
041 *
042 * <p>This is a <a
043 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based</a>
044 * class.</p>
045 *
046 * @param <V> the type of a {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
047 * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
048 *
049 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson"
050 * target="_parent">Laird Nelson</a>
051 *
052 * @see Bindings
053 */
054public final class Qualifiers<V> extends Bindings<V, Qualifier<V>> {
055
056
057  /*
058   * Static fields.
059   */
060
061
062  private static final Qualifiers<?> EMPTY = new Qualifiers<>(List.of());
063
064
065  /*
066   * Constructors.
067   */
068
069
070  private Qualifiers(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<V>> qualifiers) {
071    super(qualifiers);
072  }
073
074
075  /*
076   * Instance methods.
077   */
078
079
080  /**
081   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} with
082   * this {@link Qualifiers}' entries and an additional entry
083   * consisting of the supplied {@link Qualifier}.
084   *
085   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
086   * unless {@code qualifier} is {@code null}, in which case {@code
087   * this} will be returned.</p>
088   *
089   * @param qualifier a {@link Qualifier}; may be {@code null} in
090   * which case {@code this} will be returned
091   *
092   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with this {@link Qualifiers}'
093   * entries and an additional entry consisting of the supplied {@link
094   * Qualifier}
095   *
096   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
097   *
098   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
099   *
100   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
101   * threads.
102   *
103   * @see #plus(Iterable)
104   */
105  public final Qualifiers<V> plus(final Qualifier<V> qualifier) {
106    if (qualifier == null) {
107      return this;
108    } else if (this.isEmpty()) {
109      return of(qualifier);
110    } else {
111      return this.plus(List.of(qualifier));
112    }
113  }
114
115  /**
116   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} with
117   * this {@link Qualifiers}' entries and additional entries
118   * represented by the supplied {@code qualifiers}.
119   *
120   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
121   * unless {@code qualifier} is {@code null}, in which case {@code
122   * this} will be returned.</p>
123   *
124   * @param qualifiers additional {@link Qualifier}s; may be {@code
125   * null} in which case {@code this} will be returned
126   *
127   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with this {@link Qualifiers}'
128   * entries and additional entries represented by the supplied {@code
129   * qualifiers}
130   *
131   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
132   *
133   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
134   *
135   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
136   * threads.
137   */
138  public final Qualifiers<V> plus(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<V>> qualifiers) {
139    if (qualifiers == null) {
140      return this;
141    } else if (this.isEmpty()) {
142      return of(qualifiers);
143    }
144    final Collection<Qualifier<V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
145    for (final Qualifier<V> q : this) {
146      newQualifiers.add(q);
147    }
148    for (final Qualifier<V> q : qualifiers) {
149      newQualifiers.add(q);
150    }
151    return of(newQualifiers);
152  }
153
154  /**
155   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
156   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
157   * keys} are prefixed with the supplied {@code prefix}.
158   *
159   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
160   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
161   *
162   * @param prefix a prefix; if {@code null} then {@code this} will be returned
163   *
164   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
165   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
166   * keys} are prefixed with the supplied {@code prefix}
167   *
168   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
169   *
170   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
171   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
172   *
173   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
174   * threads
175   */
176  public final Qualifiers<V> withPrefix(final String prefix) {
177    if (prefix == null || this.isEmpty()) {
178      return this;
179    }
180    return this.withPrefix(q -> prefix + q.name());
181  }
182
183  /**
184   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
185   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
186   * keys} are produced by the supplied {@link Function}, which is
187   * expected to prepend a prefix to the original key and return the
188   * result.
189   *
190   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
191   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
192   *
193   * @param f a deterministic, idempotent {@link Function} that
194   * accepts keys drawn from this {@link Qualifiers}' {@link
195   * Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
196   * and returns a non-{@code null} prefixed version of that key; may
197   * be {@code null} in which case {@code this} will be returned
198   *
199   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
200   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
201   * keys} have been prefixed by the actions of the supplied {@link
202   * Function}
203   *
204   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
205   *
206   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
207   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
208   *
209   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
210   * threads, assuming the supplied {@link Function} is
211   */
212  public final Qualifiers<V> withPrefix(final Function<? super Qualifier<V>, ? extends String> f) {
213    if (f == null || this.isEmpty()) {
214      return this;
215    }
216    final Collection<Qualifier<V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
217    for (final Qualifier<V> q : this) {
218      newQualifiers.add(Qualifier.of(f.apply(q),
219                                     q.value(),
220                                     q.attributes(),
221                                     q.info()));
222    }
223    return of(newQualifiers);
224  }
225
226  /**
227   * Returns a {@link MethodHandleDesc} describing the constructor or
228   * {@code static} method that will be used to create a <a
229   * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/invoke/package-summary.html#condycon">dynamic
230   * constant</a> representing this {@link Qualifiers}.
231   *
232   * @return a {@link MethodHandleDesc} describing the constructor or
233   * {@code static} method that will be used to create a <a
234   * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/invoke/package-summary.html#condycon">dynamic
235   * constant</a> representing this {@link Qualifiers}
236   *
237   * @nullability This method does not, and its overrides must not,
238   * return {@code null}.
239   *
240   * @idempotency This method is, and its overrides must be,
241   * idempotent and deterministic.
242   *
243   * @threadsafety This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for
244   * concurrent use by multiple threads.
245   */
246  @Override // Bindings<V, Qualifier<V>>
247  protected final MethodHandleDesc describeConstructor() {
248    return
249      MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
250                                CD_Qualifiers,
251                                "of",
252                                MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers, CD_Iterable));
253  }

257   * Static methods.

261  /**
262   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
263   * created, whose {@link #isEmpty() isEmpty()} method will return
264   * {@code true}.
265   *
266   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
267   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
268   *
269   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
270   *
271   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
272   *
273   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
274   *
275   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
276   * threads.
277   */
278  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
279  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of() {
280    return (Qualifiers<V>)EMPTY;
281  }
282
283  /**
284   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
285   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
286   *
287   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
288   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
289   *
290   * @param qualifier the sole {@link Qualifier} the {@link
291   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
292   *
293   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
294   *
295   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code qualifier} is {@code
296   * null}
297   *
298   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
299   *
300   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
301   *
302   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
303   * threads.
304   */
305  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of(final Qualifier<V> qualifier) {
306    return of(List.of(Objects.requireNonNull(qualifier, "qualifier")));
307  }
308
309  /**
310   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
311   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
312   *
313   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
314   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
315   *
316   * @param qualifier0 the first {@link Qualifier} the {@link
317   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
318   *
319   * @param qualifier1 the second {@link Qualifier} the {@link
320   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
321   *
322   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
323   *
324   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code qualifier} is {@code
325   * null}
326   *
327   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
328   *
329   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
330   *
331   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
332   * threads.
333   */
334  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of(final Qualifier<V> qualifier0, final Qualifier<V> qualifier1) {
335    return of(List.of(qualifier0, qualifier1));
336  }
337
338  /**
339   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
340   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
341   *
342   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
343   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
344   *
345   * @param qualifiers an {@link Iterable} representing {@link
346   * Qualifier} instances the {@link Qualifiers} will contain; may be
347   * {@code null}
348   *
349   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
350   *
351   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
352   *
353   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
354   *
355   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
356   * threads.
357   */
358  public static final <V> Qualifiers<V> of(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<V>> qualifiers) {
359    if (qualifiers == null) {
360      return of();
361    }
362    final Iterator<? extends Qualifier<V>> i = qualifiers.iterator();
363    if (i.hasNext()) {
364      final Collection<Qualifier<V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
365      newQualifiers.add(i.next());
366      while (i.hasNext()) {
367        newQualifiers.add(i.next());
368      }
369      return new Qualifiers<>(newQualifiers);
370    }
371    return of();
372  }
373
374  /**
375   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
376   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
377   *
378   * @param qualifiers an {@link Iterable} representing {@link
379   * Qualifier} instances the {@link Qualifiers} will contain; may be
380   * {@code null}
381   *
382   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
383   *
384   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
385   *
386   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
387   *
388   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
389   * threads.
390   */
391  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
392  public static final Qualifiers<?> ofDisparate(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<?>> qualifiers) {
393    if (qualifiers == null) {
394      return of();
395    }
396    final Iterator<? extends Qualifier<?>> i = qualifiers.iterator();
397    if (i.hasNext()) {
398      final Collection<Qualifier<Object>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
399      newQualifiers.add((Qualifier<Object>)i.next());
400      while (i.hasNext()) {
401        newQualifiers.add((Qualifier<Object>)i.next());
402      }
403      return new Qualifiers<>(newQualifiers);
404    }
405    return of();
406  }
